	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 13th 12:58 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=600><span id=Guru>PraetorFenix</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>277 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.37]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This I feel is very misleading.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Fiery Defender also has 15 AC on it, adds about 125 HP, and allows the wielder to bash with no shield.<br><br>There are <i>very</i> few one handed weapons that will even come <i>close</i> to touching the damage of the paladin epic weapon.<br><br>The "stick with 1hs" mentatlity has always bothered me in that the 10 AC from a shield is negligable when you can increase your damage output by 50% with the epic.  Not to mention the 30 mana and 15 wisdom, which is critical in high end encounters to your effectiveness.  Also 10 SV all, which is vital to your own survival on dragons.<br><br>There are only two situations where I would use a one handed weapon over an epic or higher class two hander:<br><br>1) Frostwrath + Shield of the Dawn<br>2) Dawncaller + Shield of the Dawn<br><br>These are one handed weapons and a shield off the hardest dragons in the game, in the hardest zone in the game.  To be telling level 12 paladins that they should not get their epic because of two obscenely rare weapons that 99% of the EQ population will never see I feel is not a good choice.<br><br>On a secondary note, in the high level raiding game we are NOT the extreme defensive tanks as we seem to be made out as.  There are a plethora of level 60 warriors out there who taunt better, damage better, and tank better than paladins.  At this stage we are secondary healers, and secondary damage dealers.  When the point is reached that paladins are tanking, the raid is over, camp is called and you regroup.  We aren't tanks no matter how you cut it, we might as well be rangers with two handers if we couldn't heal and buff so well.<br><br>Just remember that tanking isn't our only role, because if you focus on that you're just a substandard meat shield.  There's a lot more to the class than auto-attack and afk. :)<br><br>To answer the original poster the epic is the <a href=HTTP://eqdb.allakhazam.com/item.html?item=3572 target=akztarg>Fiery Defender</a>, and it can only be obtained after level 46 (when you can travel to the planes).  However, due to the rarity and level limits on some encounters, you may be forced to wait until even level 60 to obtain the weapon.</p>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 65th Lord Protector<br>Ascent</td></td></tr>
